  "title": "HR Manager (Infrastructure Industry)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Our client is a well-established construction, property development and specialist engineering\nsolutions provider. Currently, they are seeking for HR Manager to be part of the team.</strong></p><p><br /><strong>JOB DIMENSION (SCOPE)</strong></p><p><strong>Strategic & Operational HR</strong></p><ul><li>Manage the full spectrum of HR activities including recruitment, payroll, performance management, and employee relations</li><li>Partner with management and operations teams to support workforce planning for plants, sites, and projects</li><li>Develop, implement, and review HR policies and procedures aligned with business needs</li></ul><p><strong>Recruitment & Manpower Planning</strong></p><ul><li>Lead <strong>end-to-end recruitment</strong> for technical, operations, and support roles</li><li>Understand manpower requirements specific to <strong>waste water treatment plants, infrastructure, environmental operations, and site-based teams</strong></li><li>Liaise with recruitment agencies and external stakeholders when required</li></ul><p><strong>Statutory Compliance & Work Passes</strong></p><ul><li>Ensure compliance with <strong>Singapore MOM regulations</strong>, Employment Act, and company policies</li><li>Manage work pass matters (WP, S Pass, EP), renewals, and cancellations</li><li>Support audits and inspections related to HR and manpower compliance</li></ul><p><strong>Employee Relations & Engagement</strong></p><ul><li>Handle employee grievances, disciplinary matters, and performance issues</li><li>Support employee engagement, retention, and welfare initiatives</li></ul><p><strong>Payroll & HR Administration</strong></p><ul><li>Oversee payroll processing, leave management, and HR documentation</li><li>Maintain accurate HR records and reporting</li></ul><p><br /><strong>JOB REQUIREMENTS</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Human Resource Management, Business Administration, or related field</li><li>8–12 years of HR experience, with managerial experience preferred</li><li>Prior experience in infrastructure, waste water treatment, utilities, environmental, plant operations, building construction, or industrial sectors is highly advantageous</li><li>Strong knowledge of Singapore employment laws and MOM regulations</li><li>Experience managing blue-collar, technical, and site-based workforce</li><li>Good leadership, communication, and problem-solving skills</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Onion Search Pte Ltd</p><p>EA License No: 24C2108</p><p>EA Personnel: Clover Lai Kah Wai</p><p>EA Personnel No: R24120119</p>",
